# Razorpay Integration Plan

This plan details the steps to integrate Razorpay for secure payments within the Cenifex booking system. It follows the exact flow requested: Backend creates the order, Frontend handles checkout, Backend verifies the payment signature.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - You will need to provide Razorpay Test Key and Secret. For this development, I'll use placeholders in [application.properties](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/resources/application.properties). You should replace them with your actual Razorpay keys.
> - The application will require a database migration (or Hibernate update) to add new columns to the `booking` table. Ensure `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto` is set to `update`.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend - Configuration & Definitions
#### [MODIFY] [pom.xml](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/pom.xml)
- Add the `razorpay-java` SDK dependency.

#### [MODIFY] [application.properties](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/resources/application.properties)
- Add `razorpay.key.id` and `razorpay.key.secret` configuration fields.

#### [MODIFY] [Booking.java](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/entity/Booking.java)
- Add `razorpayOrderId` (String)
- Add `razorpayPaymentId` (String)
- Update `status` comments to explicitly mention `PENDING`, `CONFIRMED`, `FAILED`.

#### [NEW] [PaymentVerificationRequest.java](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/dto/PaymentVerificationRequest.java)
- Create a DTO with fields: `razorpayOrderId`, `razorpayPaymentId`, `razorpaySignature`.

***

### Backend - Logic
#### [MODIFY] [BookingService.java](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/service/BookingService.java)
- Inject Razorpay API credentials.
- In [createBooking](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/controller/BookingController.java#35-44), initiate an order with Razorpay (`RazorpayClient.orders.create`).
- Save the booking with the new `razorpayOrderId` and `status = "PENDING"`.
- Return the `razorpayOrderId` and necessary keys to the controller.
- Add a new method `verifyPayment(PaymentVerificationRequest)` to compute the HMAC SHA256 signature and compare it against `razorpaySignature`. Update booking status to `CONFIRMED` or `FAILED`.

#### [MODIFY] [BookingController.java](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/controller/BookingController.java)
- Update `/api/booking/create` to return the `razorpayOrderId`.
- Add a new POST endpoint `/api/booking/verify-payment` to consume the signature verification.

***

### Frontend - UI & Validation
#### [MODIFY] [seat-selection.html](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/resources/static/seat-selection.html)
- Add `<script src="https://checkout.razorpay.com/v1/checkout.js"></script>` in the `<head>` or body.

#### [MODIFY] [seat-selection.js](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/resources/static/js/seat-selection.js)
- Update the checkout logic. Instead of just showing success, use the returned `razorpayOrderId` to initialize a Razorpay Checkout options object.
- Define `handler: function (response)` inside Razorpay options to capture `razorpay_payment_id`, `razorpay_order_id`, and `razorpay_signature`.
- Send this payload back to `/api/booking/verify-payment`.
- Handle payment failure gracefully (show alert, keep booking PENDING).

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- No automated UI tests exist for this component. I will compile the application and verify no syntax errors (`mvn clean compile`).

### Manual Verification
1. Run the Spring Boot application locally.
2. Log into the local frontend.
3. Select seats for a showtime and click "Pay Now".
4. The Razorpay test payment modal should appear.
5. Provide test payment details (e.g. Test Card provided by Razorpay or Netbanking).
6. Verify that the success callback fires, hitting `/api/booking/verify-payment`.
7. Verify that the database shows the [Booking](file:///c:/Users/akhil/Downloads/cenifex/src/main/java/com/cenifex/entity/Booking.java#8-33) record changed from `PENDING` to `CONFIRMED`.
8. Check that closing the Razorpay modal leaves the booking `PENDING` in the database.
